    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Augment contact records with HubSpot and HTTP / REST API at scale for Multi-Tool Agent (01759)\n\n**Pattern:** Data Enrichment · **Level:** Architect · **Trigger:** Scheduled\n\n## What it does\nAugment contact records with HubSpot and HTTP / REST API at scale for Multi-Tool Agent (01759). It runs automatically on a schedule.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual multi-tool agent is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nHourly Schedule → Init Cursor → Page Loop → Remove Duplicate Requests → Upsert Harvest into Notion → Tally Harvest Stats → Load Previous Snapshot → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to data enrichment without manual effort\n- Anyone automating multi-tool agent in ai\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Responds in seconds\n- Runs 24/7 in the background\n- Saves hours of manual work each week\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Google OAuth2; HubSpot private-app token; Notion integration token; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "4a066087-f465-2b96-71da-59cd30decf6a",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Failures are also parked in a dead-letter queue for replay. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 3
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -230,
        -20
      ],
      "id": "749fe994-15bb-9f19-f759-fa8799692c0a",
      "name": "🛟 Error handling & retries"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## ⏱ Rate limiting\n\nWork is batched and spaced with Wait so provider quotas aren't tripped. If you hit 429s, lower the batch size or raise the wait — throughput drops, reliability rises.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 1
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        190,
        -20
      ],
      "id": "27e45e1f-4001-071b-d2f3-b5112936ae77",
      "name": "⏱ Rate limiting"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🧹 Data quality\n\nDedupe/diff steps make re-runs safe: the same input twice will not create duplicate records. If you change the key fields, clear n8n's dedupe memory (node → 'Clear stored keys') before the next run.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 1
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
